## 1. Use and Distribution
Anyone can use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software for beneficial purposes. These freedoms aim to promote access to information and the sharing of knowledge among individuals and communities. Any use for illegal purposes or purposes not pleasing to Allah is strictly prohibited.

## 2. Modifications and Derivatives
Modified or derivative versions of the Software must also comply with these license terms. When modifications or derivatives are created, the original software must be credited. This aims to prevent the loss of effort and to avoid potential misuse. Improvements must be shared and not kept private.

## 3. Attribution
When using the Software, it is expected that you appropriately attribute the original authors and contributors of the software. Attribution is important to recognize and encourage those who contribute to the dissemination of knowledge.

## 4. Commercial Use
The Software can be used for commercial purposes. However, it is encouraged that a portion of the proceeds be donated to educational, research, and community benefit activities. This supports the principle of giving back to the community.

## 5. Disclaimer of Liability
The Software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. The use of the Software is entirely at the user's own risk. The authors and contributors are not liable for any damages arising from the use of the Software.
